==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reverent
<hw>Rev"er*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>reverens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>revereri</ets>.
See <er>Revere</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Disposed to revere;
impressed with reverence; submissive; humble; respectful; <as>as,
<ex>reverent</ex> disciples</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧They . . . prostrate fell
before him <xex>reverent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressing reverence, veneration, devotion, or
submission; <as>as, <ex>reverent</ex> words; <ex>reverent</ex>
behavior</as>.</def> <rj><au>Joye.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reverential</ent>⟦br⟧
